	abstract = {We present a catalog covering 1.62 deg{\textless}{SUP}{\textgreater}2{\textless}/{SUP}{\textgreater} of the {COSMOS}/{UltraVISTA} field with point-spread function ({PSF}) matched photometry in 30 photometric bands. The catalog covers the wavelength range 0.15-24 μm including the available {GALEX}, Subaru, Canada-France-Hawaii Telescope, {VISTA}, and Spitzer data. Catalog sources have been selected from the {DR}1 {UltraVISTA} K{\textless}{SUB}{\textgreater}s{\textless}/{SUB}{\textgreater} band imaging that reaches a depth of K {\textless}{SUB}{\textgreater} s, tot{\textless}/{SUB}{\textgreater} = 23.4 {AB} (90\% completeness). The {PSF}-matched catalog is generated using position-dependent {PSFs} ensuring accurate colors across the entire field. Also included is a catalog of photometric redshifts (z {\textless}{SUB}{\textgreater}phot{\textless}/{SUB}{\textgreater}) for all galaxies computed with the {EAZY} code. Comparison with spectroscopy from the {zCOSMOS} 10k bright sample shows that up to z {\textasciitilde} 1.5 the z {\textless}{SUB}{\textgreater}phot{\textless}/{SUB}{\textgreater} are accurate to ∆z/(1 + z) = 0.013, with a catastrophic outlier fraction of only 1.6\%. The z {\textless}{SUB}{\textgreater}phot{\textless}/{SUB}{\textgreater} also show good agreement with the z {\textless}{SUB}{\textgreater}phot{\textless}/{SUB}{\textgreater} from the {NEWFIRM} Medium Band Survey out to z {\textasciitilde} 3. A catalog of stellar masses and stellar population parameters for galaxies determined using the {FAST} spectral energy distribution fitting code is provided for all galaxies. Also included are rest-frame U - V and V - J colors, L {\textless}{SUB}{\textgreater}2800{\textless}/{SUB}{\textgreater} and L {\textless}{SUB}{\textgreater}{IR}{\textless}/{SUB}{\textgreater}. The {UVJ} color-color diagram confirms that the galaxy bi-modality is well-established out to z {\textasciitilde} 2. Star-forming galaxies also obey a star-forming "main sequence" out to z {\textasciitilde} 2.5, and this sequence evolves in a manner consistent with previous measurements. The {COSMOS}/{UltraVISTA} K{\textless}{SUB}{\textgreater}s{\textless}/{SUB}{\textgreater} -selected catalog covers a unique parameter space in both depth, area, and multi-wavelength coverage and promises to be a useful tool for studying the growth of the galaxy population out to z {\textasciitilde} 3-4. .},
