B}{\textgreater}0{\textless}/{SUB}{\textgreater}{\textasciitilde}=73+/-8 km s{\textless}{SUP}{\textgreater}-1{\textless}/{SUP}{\textgreater} Mpc{\textless}{SUP}{\textgreater}-1{\textless}/{SUP}{\textgreater}. More complicated lenses with multiple components or strong perturbations from nearby clusters, like {RX} J0911+0551 and Q0957+561, are easily recognized because they have significantly different coefficients.},
